<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 97-03-04 - 2-Leaf Parabolic (Taper Leaf) Steer Axle Springs</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi970304" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>97-03-04</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>September, 1997</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>SPRINGS</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>2-Leaf Parabolic (Taper Leaf) Steer Axle Springs</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>8100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9800</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Effective July, 1997, 2-leaf parabolic, or taper leaf, steer axle springs are standard on 8100,
                    9300, and 9800SFA Models as part of Navistar's continuous product improvement process. These springs
                    may also be retrofitted on the 9670 Model.
                </para>
                <para>As with 2-leaf springs used in other Navistar Models, the 2-leaf parabolic (taper leaf) spring may
                    appear flat or slightly arched at the spring shackle end which is normal.
                </para>
                <para>The static deflection rate for the 2-leaf parabolic (taper leaf) springs is equivalent to the
                    3-leaf springs they replace, but the dynamic deflection rate is less, resulting in improved ride
                    quality.
                </para>
                <para>The 2-leaf parabolic (taper leaf) springs can be retrofitted on older 8100, 9670, 9300, and
                    9800SFA Models, however, they should not be intermixed with 3-leaf springs on the same chassis.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
